AMENDMENTS TO LB1181
Introduced by Judiciary.
1 1. On page 9, strike beginning with ", as" in line 10 through
2 "death" in line 12.
3 2. On page 10, strike lines 24 through 28 and insert the following
4 new subdivision:
5 "(c) In a case involving abuse as defined in section 42-903, to
6 submit a written statement to be considered by the court during any bond
7 modification proceeding, when time permits;".
8 3. On page 11, strike beginning with the period in line 3 through
9 "finding" in line 5; strike lines 9 through 14 and insert the following
10 new subdivisions:
11 "(f)(i) To read, or to appoint a representative to read, his or her
12 written impact statement aloud at the sentencing proceeding. The court
13 may impose reasonable limitations, such as limits on the duration of such
14 reading, to ensure the orderly and fair administration of justice.
15 However, such limits shall not impede a victim's ability to deliver an
16 oral statement if the victim so desires.
17 (ii) For purposes of subdivision (3)(f)(i) of this section, in the
18 case of a homicide, the term victim also includes any survivor who, as
19 determined on a case-by-case basis, suffered severe emotional harm as a
20 result of the victim's death;"; and in line 20, after "bond" insert ",
21 when time permits such notice".
